import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['quadrant'] = data['quadrant'].astype(str)
    sns.scatterplot(x='x', y='y', hue='quadrant', size='count', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between X and Y?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['x'] = pd.to_datetime(data['x'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='x', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['x'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['x'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of X?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
